      &lt;p&gt;New to me. Obvious to most people. &lt;a href=&quot;#fnref:1&quot; class=&quot;reversefootnote&quot; role=&quot;doc-backlink&quot;&gt;&amp;#8617;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li id=&quot;fn:2&quot; role=&quot;doc-endnote&quot;&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Not including when my laptop downloaded dependencies and I was scrolling Reddit. &lt;a href=&quot;#fnref:2&quot; class=&quot;reversefootnote&quot; role=&quot;doc-backlink&quot;&gt;&amp;#8617;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li id=&quot;fn:3&quot; role=&quot;doc-endnote&quot;&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;I have no reason to &lt;em&gt;actually&lt;/em&gt; use Git properly. &lt;a href=&quot;#fnref:3&quot; class=&quot;reversefootnote&quot; role=&quot;doc-backlink&quot;&gt;&amp;#8617;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li id=&quot;fn:4&quot; role=&quot;doc-endnote&quot;&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;At some point when testing, I messed up and the hook started copying all of &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;~&lt;/code&gt; into my repository. That scared me a lot - what if &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;rm&lt;/code&gt; had run in &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;~&lt;/code&gt; instead of &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;cp&lt;/code&gt;? After that, I decided I wasn’t OK with the hook running outside my repository directory. &lt;a href=&quot;#fnref:4&quot; class=&quot;reversefootnote&quot; role=&quot;doc-backlink&quot;&gt;&amp;#8617;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;/ol&gt;
